#include 'template.wml'

<points>
<li>
Script-Fu enables to write GIMP Scripts and PDB entries in Scheme.
</li>

<li>
The Scheme scripts reside in ~/.gimp-2.2/scripts. (Replace 2.2 with the
current version of GIMP)
</li>

<li>
Whenever changed they need to be refreshed by selecting

<menupath>
<tt>
&lt;Toolbox&gt; -&gt; Xtns -&gt; Script-Fu -&gt; Refresh
</tt>
</menupath>
</li>

<li>
Besides that, GIMP sports an interactive Script-Fu Console.
</li>

</points>

